{
  "text": "The environment of the articular space has been a subject of debate and the question has been raised over time as to what oxygen tension is present in the joint space. It has been suggested that articular spaces may have lower oxygen content than other locations in the body [CITATION_1] . P. acnes typically grows better under anaerobic than aerobic conditions. Our observation that P. acnes hyaluronidase is produced under anaerobic but not aerobic conditions (Figure 4 ) may have clinical relevance in the context of the environment in joint spaces and possibly in biofilms.",
